posts.name: G3 6740
posts.cooked:
Hi, kinda repeating myself here but iv’e been having trouble getting proper commes with the driver station wirelessly, so iv’e tried setting up our robot radio from scratch but i keep getting stuck at configurring it, none of the ways to do it trough a browser seem to work and when evey i try to configure throgh the VH network assistent tool, it gives me the message ‘‘configuration failed for interface, ensure that the adapter is plugged into the ds or RIO port of the radio’’ I dont know what adaptor they mean but i’m connected via ethernet to the radio

can anyone help? thank you

posts.name: Brody Anderson
posts.cooked: Have you updated the software to the correct version already? I remember having similar issues a while ago, for us I believe it was fixed once we updated the software again and simply let it sit for a few minutes. Which port is your ethernet connected to?

posts.name: G3 6740
posts.cooked: i think its on the right softwere version, how do i check? my ethernet is connected to the DS port on the radio#

posts.name: Brody Anderson
posts.cooked: Under the firmware upload section there should be a little name box that says “VH-109” followed by a version number. Have you uploaded firmware yet?

posts.name: G3 6740
posts.cooked: i can’t get to the configuration page in order to see…

posts.name: Brody Anderson
posts.cooked: Ah okay, could you send a picture of your current set up and the VH network assistant tool?

posts.name: G3 6740
posts.cooked: sorry if its a bit unclear

posts.name: Brody Anderson
posts.cooked: Just to confirm, that ds port is running to the computer right?

posts.name: Brody Anderson
posts.cooked: Do you have a different laptop you can try it with?

posts.name: Brody Anderson
posts.cooked: From what I can see, there’s an issue with either your enet cord, your radio port, your computers port, or the radio itself needs some time to sit
